 316:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c **** /** @defgroup UARTEx_Exported_Functions_Group3 Peripheral Control functions
 317:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   * @brief    Extended Peripheral Control functions
 318:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****   *
 319:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c **** @verbatim
 320:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****  ===============================================================================
 321:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****                       ##### Peripheral Control functions #####
 322:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****  ===============================================================================
 323:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****     [..] This section provides the following functions:
 324:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****      (+) HAL_MultiProcessorEx_AddressLength_Set() API optionally sets the UART node address
 325:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****          detection length to more than 4 bits for multiprocessor address mark wake up.
 326:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****      (+) HAL_UARTEx_StopModeWakeUpSourceConfig() API defines the wake-up from stop mode
 327:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****          trigger: address match, Start Bit detection or RXNE bit status.
 328:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****      (+) HAL_UARTEx_EnableStopMode() API enables the UART to wake up the MCU from stop mode
 329:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****      (+) HAL_UARTEx_DisableStopMode() API disables the above functionality
 330:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****      (+) HAL_UARTEx_EnableFifoMode() API enables the FIFO mode
 331:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****      (+) HAL_UARTEx_DisableFifoMode() API disables the FIFO mode
 332:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****      (+) HAL_UARTEx_SetTxFifoThreshold() API sets the TX FIFO threshold
 333:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****      (+) HAL_UARTEx_SetRxFifoThreshold() API sets the RX FIFO threshold
 334:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c **** 
 335:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****     [..] This subsection also provides a set of additional functions providing enhanced reception
 336:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****     services to user. (For example, these functions allow application to handle use cases
 337:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****     where number of data to be received is unknown).
 338:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c **** 
 339:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****     (#) Compared to standard reception services which only consider number of received
 340:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****         data elements as reception completion criteria, these functions also consider additional ev
 341:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****         as triggers for updating reception status to caller :
 342:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****        (++) Detection of inactivity period (RX line has not been active for a given period).
 343:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****           (+++) RX inactivity detected by IDLE event, i.e. RX line has been in idle state (normally
 344:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****                for 1 frame time, after last received byte.
 345:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****           (+++) RX inactivity detected by RTO, i.e. line has been in idle state
 346:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****                for a programmable time, after last received byte.
 347:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****        (++) Detection that a specific character has been received.
 348:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c **** 
 349:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****     (#) There are two modes of transfer:
 350:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****        (++) Blocking mode: The reception is performed in polling mode, until either expected number
 351:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****            or till IDLE event occurs. Reception is handled only during function execution.
 352:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****            When function exits, no data reception could occur. HAL status and number of actually re
 353:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****            are returned by function after finishing transfer.
 354:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****        (++) Non-Blocking mode: The reception is performed using Interrupts or DMA.
 355:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****            These API's return the HAL status.
 356:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****            The end of the data processing will be indicated through the
 357:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****            dedicated UART IRQ when using Interrupt mode or the DMA IRQ when using DMA mode.
 358:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_uart_ex.c ****            The HAL_UARTEx_RxEventCallback() user callback will be executed during Receive process
